text.section:
"Program provider" means a nonprofit organization that, as determined by the State Superintendent:
Exclusively focuses on the improvement of performance management and the use of technology for other nonprofit organizations and schools;
Has demonstrated experience in providing a range of assistance to nonprofit community-based organizations and schools including:
Assessing performance and the use of technology;
Developing recommendations to improve performance and the use of technology; and
Implementing those recommendations;
Has demonstrated the ability to identify areas for program improvement related to the use of technology in classrooms and by administrators;
Has demonstrated the ability to develop an implementation plan for recommended improvements;
Has demonstrated the ability to assist with and provide on-site, hands-on guidance with the implementation of the recommendations; and
Has demonstrated the ability to create an on-line community that allows teachers, parents, policymakers, and other stakeholders to communicate and provide support during and following the assessment and implementation process.
